# ── CHAIN privacy firewall ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The repo ships the MECHANISM, never your data. CHAIN owns two writable roots:
# chain_home (default ~/.chain, outside the repo) and the review root (in-repo,
# below). Your sources and canon are referenced in place and never copied here. If
# any of these ever show up tracked, stop and check before committing.

# Your real, private data and config — real files + symlinks to their canonical
# homes (e.g. ~/Documents/Writing), visible for inspection, never tracked.
PRIVATE__YOUR_FILES_GITIGNORED/

# Generated output waiting on human review — drafts, packets. Canonical, visible
# location; never tracked.
__READY_TO_REVIEW__PRIVATE_GITIGNORED/

# Your real, path-bearing config (copy of chain.config.example.yaml)
*.config.local.yaml

# Personal-identifier denylist read by the local pre-commit firewall hook
*denylist.local.txt

# chain_home when kept local (learned state, cache). The default ~/.chain lives
# outside the repo; this covers the demo's ./.chain too.
.chain/

# The SYNTHETIC demo home is committed on purpose so the repo runs with no real data.
!examples/demo-home/
!examples/demo-home/**

# Credentials / session
.env
*.secret
credentials*.json
session*.json

# ── ordinary noise ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.DS_Store
*.egg-info/
.venv/
